cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the semantics of linear logic and lambda calculus. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the execution time of lambda terms. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is relevant as the paper introduces a non-idempotent intersection type system. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) could be a possible category as the paper discusses the relationship between type derivations/types and execution time, which could be relevant to software performance optimization. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the formal semantics of lambda calculus and intersection types.
